Here's the sample payload from the staging endpoint for the docs:

```json
{
  "customer": {
    "id": "cus_00000000",
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john.doe@example.com",
    "phone": "+1-555-0123",
    "address": {
      "line1": "123 Main St",
      "city": "Anytown",
      "state": "CA",
      "postal_code": "94000"
    }
  },
  "status": "active"
}
```

Let me know if you want me to swap in Jane Doe for the secondary example.

Here's the fixture I'm using for the unit test — feel free to copy:

```json
{
  "user": {
    "id": "usr_00000001",
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john.doe@example.com",
    "phone": "+1-555-0100",
    "address": {
      "line1": "123 Example St",
      "city": "Springfield",
      "state": "CA",
      "zip": "00000"
    }
  },
  "created_at": "2024-01-01T00:00:00Z"
}
```

LMK if you want me to add a Jane Doe record too for the multi-user case.
